 are traveling in Jerusalem with the wife\u2019s mother. Unfortunately, the mother-in-law suddenly passes away.\n\nThey go to a local funeral director, who tells them: \u201cYou can have her buried here in the Holy Land for $5,000, or we can ship her back home for $20,000.\u201d\n\nThe husband thinks for a moment and says, \u201cWe\u2019ll ship her home.\u201d\n\nThe funeral director, a bit surprised, asks, \u201cWhy spend $20,000 to send her home when you could bury her here in such a sacred place for much less?\u201d\n\nThe husband leans in and says, \u201cLook, I\u2019ve heard the stories. A man was buried here 2,000 years ago and came back to life. I\u2019m not taking any chances.\u201d", "author": "DemPanicAtTheDisco", "created": 1775235606015, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "DeploraBen", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "A little Easter weekend joke for everyone... ", "last_comment_created": 1775245701448, "content": "<p>A husband and wife are traveling in Jerusalem with the wife\u2019s mother. Unfortunately, the mother-in-law suddenly passes away.</p>\n<p>They go to a local funeral director, who tells them: \u201cYou can have her buried here in the Holy Land for $5,000, or we can ship her back home for $20,000.\u201d</p>\n<p>The husband thinks for a moment and says, \u201cWe\u2019ll ship her home.\u201d</p>\n<p>The funeral director, a bit surprised, asks, \u201cWhy spend $20,000 to send her home when you could bury her here in such a sacred place for much less?\u201d</p>\n<p>The husband leans in and says, \u201cLook, I\u2019ve heard the stories. A man was buried here 2,000 years ago and came back to life. I\u2019m not taking any chances.\u201d</p>\n", "score_down":